# Organizational Structure & Security

Provisions the business unit / owner team / Entra security group / role-mapping layer for data isolation and group-based ownership. Runs AFTER schema + the Collaborator role (`07-dataverse-schema`); consumes `orgStructure` in `dataverse/planning-payload.json` (derived in `00b`/`00c`).

## Plugin gap — agent drives this
The Dataverse-skills plugin doesn't document BU/team creation:
- BUs & teams → plugin's bundled Python SDK (`DataverseClient.records.create("businessunit"|"team", ...)`), reusing the active PAC profile.
- Entra groups → `az ad group` / Graph (Dataverse can't create these).
- Always reuse OOB `businessunit` / `team` / `role` — never custom-model org structure or authorization (`07a`).

## When NOT to build it
Skip for flat, org-wide visibility — a single root BU with user-owned records suffices. Build only for a real captured isolation / group-ownership need.

## Golden sequence
1. Entra groups first (AAD teams need the object id): `az ad group create`. Reuse existing; record `entraObjectId` back.
2. Business units parent-first (`parentbusinessunitid@odata.bind`); never a second root.
3. Owner teams (`teamtype: 0`) after their BU. AAD team = `azureactivedirectoryobjectid` + `membershiptype`; membership flows from Entra.
4. Role associations via N:N `teamroles_association` — use the role copy whose `_businessunitid_value` matches the team's BU. Roles must exist (`07`).
5. User assignment via `dv-security`: `pac admin assign-user --user <email> --role "<RoleName>" --environment <url>`.

## orgStructure payload
`businessUnits[{name,parentName}]`, `securityGroups[{displayName,mailNickname,entraObjectId}]`, `teams[{name,businessUnitName,teamType,membershipSource,securityGroupDisplayName}]`, `roleMappings[{teamName,roleName,scope}]`.

## Key rules
Idempotent everywhere (`records.get` by name / `az ad group list` before create). Don't over-isolate. Roles before teams. Parents before children. Entra groups are out of Dataverse. Production membership via Entra groups, not scripts.
